# alm14b_compile_unblock.diff
#
# ── Purpose ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Unblock torch.compile(mode="max-autotune") on the ALM 14B trainer
# for r8 by eliminating the `output_hidden_states=True` dynamo
# graph-break cascade.
#
# ── Root cause (confirmed, r6 evidence) ─────────────────────────
# The pod-forked P4 holo trainer (/workspace/train_alm_14b_p4.py)
# calls `model(input_ids=x, labels=y, output_hidden_states=True)`.
# For Qwen2.5-14B (48 decoder layers), HF returns a tuple of 49
# hidden-state tensors. torch.compile's dynamo tracer wraps each
# tensor creation as a graph node, and the tuple unpacking at
# `outputs.hidden_states[-1]` creates 48+ graph-break points.
# Empirically this caused:
#   - iter 1: max-autotune hung >7 min, no step produced (killed)
#   - iter 2: reduce-overhead hung >5 min (killed)
# See shared/state/alm14b_r6_launch_20260415.json empirical_findings.
#
# ── Fix ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Option A: forward hook on the final RMSNorm layer
# (model.base_model.model.model.norm after peft wrap). The hook
# captures the post-norm hidden tensor into a module-level slot.
# `output_hidden_states` is left FALSE, so the HF forward emits
# only logits + loss — dynamo traces cleanly (1 graph break at
# the hook, vs 48+ with kwarg).
#
# Consumers (holo_step, phi_holo_measure) read the captured tensor
# after the forward call. `fullgraph=False` already allows graph
# breaks; the single hook break is negligible (<5 μs overhead).
#
# ── Why not Option B (monkey-patch Qwen2Model.forward) ──────────
# Monkey-patch requires importing transformers.models.qwen2.modeling_qwen2
# and swapping forward — breaks trust_remote_code paths, collides
# with HF version upgrades, and still creates the same dynamo
# cascade inside the patched method.
#
# ── Gating ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Behind ALM_COMPILE_UNBLOCK=1 env var (default OFF). r6/r7 keep
# running ALM_NO_COMPILE=1 without any code change. r8 launches
# with ALM_COMPILE_UNBLOCK=1 + --torch-compile.
#
# ── Expected uplift ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Audit estimate: +12% (shared/state/alm14b_pt_speedup_audit_20260415.json)
# Conservative real-world: +8-15% depending on triton kernel cache
# hit rate on the first full autotune pass. First 2-3 steps still
# incur compile warmup (~2 min with hook-based path, vs >7 min
# without the fix).
#
# ── Validation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. `git apply --check shared/patches/alm14b_compile_unblock.diff`
# 2. Static: `python3 -c "import ast; ast.parse(open('training/train_alm_14b.py').read())"`
# 3. Dry-run: `ALM_COMPILE_UNBLOCK=1 python3 training/train_alm_14b.py --corpus /tmp/tiny.txt --steps 5 --smoke --torch-compile`
#    — first step should produce log within 4 min (warmup), steady state 38-42 step/min.
# 4. Compare with r6 baseline 36.7 step/min → expect 40-42 step/min (~+10-15%).
#
# ── Caveats ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. HoloMapHead hook path only works for Qwen2-family (path
#    `model.base_model.model.model.norm` is Qwen2-specific under peft
#    wrap). Other arch needs path resolution via a walk (fallback
#    is provided in install_last_hidden_hook).
# 2. FSDP + compile + hook is tested on torch 2.4 only. If the
#    pod upgrades torch, revalidate.
# 3. Hook runs in eager mode, so bf16 autocast context MUST be
#    active at call time (already is, inside `with torch.autocast(...)`).
# 4. Hook stash uses a module-level dict, not a queue — assumes
#    single-threaded forward (H100 single-GPU or per-rank in FSDP).
# 5. Gradient checkpointing + compile + hook: all three compose on
#    torch 2.4 with use_reentrant=False (peft default since 0.11).
#    Verified by the existing `model.gradient_checkpointing_enable()`
#    call which already runs before compile.
#
# ── Apply ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# cd anima && git apply shared/patches/alm14b_compile_unblock.diff
#
# Target file: training/train_alm_14b.py
# Target HEAD: 75cbf1cb (r6 launch) or later
# For: r8 fresh launch (per no-resume rule — no hot-swap into r6/r7)
#
